# Setup

All of this is required BEFORE doing anything else.
Some of Vim's plugins require the tools here
to compile. Without the setup step, you're
left to do it on your own. Good luck.

- Create symlinks
    - Vim
        ln -s ~/programs/config/vim/.vimrc ~/.vimrc
    - Bash
        ln -s ~/programs/config/bash/.bashrc ~/.bashrc

- Get xbacklight
    sudo apt-get install xbacklight

- Get CMake
    sudo apt-get install cmake

- Get rake
    sudo apt-get install rake

- Get ruby
    sudo apt-get install ruby-dev

- Get python
    sudo apt-get install python-dev

- Get exuberant ctags
    sudo apt-get install exuberant-ctags

# Vim

- Get a decent version of vim
    sudo apt-get install vim-gnome

- Remove the shit version of vim and link the new one
    sudo rm -rf /usr/local/bin/vim
    ln -s /usr/bin/vim.gnome /usr/local/bin/vim

- get pathogen
    mkdir -p ~/.vim/autoload ~/.vim/bundle && \
    curl -LSso ~/.vim/autoload/pathogen.vim https://tpo.pe/pathogen.vim

- Get all of our plugins
    - Command-t
        git clone https://github.com/wincent/command-t
        cd ~/.vim/bundle/command-t
        sudo apt-get install ruby-dev
        rake make

    - Syntastic
        cd ~/.vim/bundle && \
        git clone https://github.com/scrooloose/syntastic.git

    - Tagbar
        cd ~/.vim/bundle
        git clone https://github.com/majutsushi/tagbar

    - YouCompleteMe
        cd ~/.vim/bundle
        git clone https://github.com/valloric/youcompleteme
        cd youcompleteme
        git submodule update --init --recursive
        ./install.py --clang-completer

    - Vim-Surround
        cd ~/.vim/bundle
        git clone git://github.com/tpope/vim-surround.git

    - Vimwiki
        cd ~/.vim/bundle
        git clone https://github.com/vimwiki/vimwiki

